<h2>Demos of HTML with Embedded Scriptlets</h2>
<p>
These demos all do pretty much the same thing, except that each uses a different scripting engine. They're here to show you that the engines
are installed correctly on your system, and as examples of how to write scriptlets for each engine. Note that at the top of each
page you will see a timestamp -- this is used to test caching mode, during which the timestamp should stay constant for 5 seconds, no matter
how many times you refresh the page. See <a href="performance.page">performance notes</a> for an explanation of the difference between caching and streaming mode.
</p>

